Derived code
------------

1. src/grisu2.rs
   A line-faithful Rust port of fpconv
   (https://github.com/night-shift/fpconv), including its formatting
   modifications to Grisu2. License: Boost Software License 1.0,
   reproduced in LICENSE-BSL-1.0. The Grisu2 algorithm itself is from
   Florian Loitsch, "Printing Floating-Point Numbers Quickly and
   Accurately with Integers" (PLDI 2010).

2. src/float.rs and src/el_table.rs
   Correctly rounded decimal-to-double conversion (the Clinger exact
   fast path and the Eisel-Lemire algorithm with its 128-bit
   powers-of-five table) ported from fast_float
   (https://github.com/fastfloat/fast_float) and fast_double_parser
   (https://github.com/lemire/fast_double_parser), Daniel Lemire et
   al. Upstream is dual-licensed Apache-2.0/MIT; this crate uses it
   under Apache-2.0, reproduced in LICENSE-APACHE-2.0.

3. src/stage1.rs
   Structural-indexing techniques from simdjson
   (https://github.com/simdjson/simdjson), Daniel Lemire, Geoff
   Langdale and contributors: the odd/even backslash-run escape
   resolution, the shufti nibble-table character classification and
   its class-bit tables, and the unconditional-write bit-flatten
   loop. License: Apache-2.0, reproduced in LICENSE-APACHE-2.0.

4. The eight-digit multiply-reduce integer parser in src/scalars.rs
   (parse_8digits_le), from the fast_float / simdjson lineage. Covered
   with item 2/3 under LICENSE-APACHE-2.0.

Architectural lineage (ideas, no copied code)
---------------------------------------------

- src/cursor.rs follows the fused single-pass byte-cursor architecture
  proven by yyjson (https://github.com/ibireme/yyjson, MIT).
- The two-stage index-then-drive pipeline follows the design described
  in "Parsing Gigabytes of JSON per Second" (Langdale & Lemire, 2019)
  and implemented by simdjson and simd-json
  (https://github.com/simd-lite/simd-json).
- Escape-emission branch layout conclusions were reached independently
  and later found to match sonic-rs
  (https://github.com/cloudwego/sonic-rs, Apache-2.0).
